Pattern Printing – C Programming (Advanced Practice Set)
## Introduction

This section focuses on advanced pattern printing problems in C, designed to strengthen logic building using nested loops, spacing control, and step-by-step problem decomposition. These patterns are commonly used in coding interviews, competitive programming basics, and aptitude-based coding tests.
Practicing these helps you think in structured loops and improves debugging and logical clarity.

Topics Covered
Nested loops (advanced usage)
Star and number patterns
Pyramid and inverted pyramids
Space manipulation logic
Symmetry-based patterns
Floyd-style and incremental patterns
Logical breakdown of complex outputs

